Subject: Let's Connect About Your Application

Body:
<html><body style="font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;color:#222222;font-size:12px;">
<p>Dear <strong>[applicant_first_name]</strong>,</p>

<p>Thank you so much for applying for the <strong>[job_title]</strong> role at <strong>Outsourced Pro Global</strong>. We're excited to learn more about you and share what makes our team a great place to grow.</p>

<p>We'd love to invite you for a <strong>[interview_duration_text] Zoom first interview</strong> with our Recruitment Specialist. This is a great chance for us to get to know each other better and see if this role and our company are the right fit for you.</p>

<p><strong>Interview details:</strong><br>
Date: [Date]<br>
Time: [Time] [Timezone]<br>
Zoom Link: [Link]</p>

<p style="white-space:pre-line;"><strong>Meeting guests:</strong><br>[guest_list_text]</p>

<p>To help you feel confident and prepared, here are <strong>a few tips for a smooth and successful interview</strong>:</p>

<ul>
<li>Take some time to review the <em><strong>job description</strong></em> and learn more <strong>about our client company: <a href="https://freedompropertyinvestors.com.au/">Freedom Property Investors</a>.</strong></li>
<li>Make sure your <em><strong>internet connection, camera, and microphone</strong></em> are <em>working properly</em> ahead of time.</li>
<li>Choose a <em><strong>quiet, distraction-free space</strong></em> where you can focus comfortably.</li>
<li>We recommend joining the meeting 5-10 minutes early.</li>
<li>Be ready to share your experiences, achievements, and how your skills align with the role.</li>
<li>Prepare a few questions - this is a great way to show your interest and learn more about the opportunity.</li>
</ul>

<p>Please also <strong>avoid the following during the interview</strong>:</p>

<ul>
<li>Joining the interview from a noisy public place, while travelling, or in an environment with frequent interruptions.</li>
<li>Turning off your camera unless this has been discussed and agreed upon with the recruiter beforehand.</li>
<li>Multitasking, taking other calls, checking emails, or engaging in other activities that may distract you during the interview.</li>
<li>Using inappropriate language or speaking negatively about previous employers, managers, colleagues, or clients.</li>
<li>Having another person answer questions, provide prompts, or participate in the interview on your behalf.</li>
<li>Using AI tools, chatbots, transcription assistants, or external resources to generate, suggest, or answer interview questions.</li>
<li>Missing the interview without prior notice. If you need to reschedule, please inform us as early as possible so alternative arrangements can be made.</li>
</ul>

<p>If you have any questions, please feel free to reply to this email - we're happy to assist.</p>

<p>We're excited to connect with you and wish you the best as you prepare for your interview.</p>

[signature]
</body></html>
